<SP>
<SPEAKER><HI>Mrs.</HI> GROVES.</SPEAKER>
<P>I, Sir will venture to an&s;wer for Mi&s;s <HI>Lovele&s;s,</HI> that &s;he will think as you very &s;en&s;ibly advi&s;e her: &s;enti|ments &s;imilar to your's &s;he expre&s;&s;ed to me before you came, and I doubt not her per&s;evering in re&s;olutions that are calculated to render both her&s;elf and her friends happy.</P>
