<SP>
<SPEAKER><HI>Mrs.</HI> GROVES.</SPEAKER>
<P>No, my dears; I am thankful that there is no cau&s;e to apprehend my being reduced to &s;o di&s;agreeable an alternative on your accounts, but I much fear there will be a nece&s;&s;ity of &s;ending away Mi&s;s <HI>Rawlings;</HI> &s;he is quite incorrigible, and though I &s;hall be very &s;orry to di&s;tre&s;s her worthy mother-in-law, yet I cannot ri&s;que the injury her example may be to my other &s;cholars.</P>
