<SP>
<SPEAKER>M<HI>r.</HI> LOVELESS.</SPEAKER>
<P>I am &s;orry, madam, you have among your young ladies one &s;o little de&s;erving. It is to be lamented that children are &s;o apt to be led by bad examples, when they may always, i&s; they plea&s;e, &s;et a good one before their eyes. I have now, <HI>Cartwright,</HI> &s;omething to &s;ay to you. [<HI>She ri&s;es from her <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> very re&s;pectfully</HI>] Sit down; I look upon you a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> a <HI>friend<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>dome&s;tic,</HI>
