<OPENER><SALUTE>Madam,</SALUTE></OPENER>
<P><HI>I will no longer deceive you, as the purpo&s;e for which I profe&s;&s;ed my&s;elf your lover is de&s;troyed by your mother's going abroad, and taking my relation Mrs. Carter, with her, who, I find, has &s;ince left her. To be a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">artaker of the fe&s;tivity at your hou&s;e, was my original motive for coming thither; and the attention I paid to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> was with a view of preventing your betraying our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> If you are bent on a trip to</HI> Sotland <HI>you mu&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">u&s;e another companion; for I have no money to &s;pare <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;uch expeditions, nor any inclination to involve my&s;elf <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> by marrying a fine lady, I therefore take <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> leave of you, and am, Madam,</HI></P>
<CLOSER><SIGNED>Your humble &s;ervant.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
